tinue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  \"unknown_files\": [\"build.rs\"],\n  \"split_candidates\": [\n    \"Consider splitting: 3 files touch different packages (swim, planedit, aiclient)\"\n  ],\n  \"merge_candidates\": []\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Native Waveplan Input\n\nThe current `ContextCandidate` JSON path is the low-level estimator interface.\nIt is appropriate for tests and hand-authored advanced usage, but it is not the\nintended normal workflow for Waveplan users.\n\nNormal Waveplan usage should be:\n\n```bash\npython waveplan-cli context estimate \\","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"docs/superpowers/specs/2026-05-13-context-sizer-design.md","time":{"start":1778783707114,"end":1778783707135}},"id":"prt_e27c55fe900234fUCOfNNqy6HP","sessionID":"ses_1d83af79fffedWQViHmEZd7IV3","messageID":"msg_e27c54083002xJko7hJNX6Zrl1"}}
