{"type":"text","timestamp":1778783728809,"sessionID":"ses_1d83af79fffedWQViHmEZd7IV3","part":{"id":"prt_e27c597a2001yiAl4F86yEI6H0","messageID":"msg_e27c5842b001s16ql4kesSRTe0","sessionID":"ses_1d83af79fffedWQViHmEZd7IV3","type":"text","text":"Let me analyze what I have:\n\n1. **T1.2 task**: \"Implement task and unit mapping\" - this is the implementation task for the adapter\n2. **Existing code**: The `waveplan.go` file already has `FromWaveplanTask` and `FromWaveplanUnit` functions implemented\n3. **Existing tests**: The `waveplan_test.go` file has comprehensive tests already written (T1.1 was \"Write adapter tests first\")\n\nLooking at the code, it seems like the implementation is already done! The adapter has:\n- `FromWaveplanTask` - converts a Waveplan task to ContextCandidate\n\n\n- `FromWaveplanUnit` - converts a Waveplan unit to ContextCandidate\n- `loadPlan` - loads execution-waves JSON\n- `resolveDocRefs` - resolves doc_refs through doc_index\n- `dedupSorted` - deduplicates and sorts file lists\n- `collapseTaskDeps` - collapses external dependencies from unit-level edges\n\nThe tests are also comprehensive, covering file resolution, doc_ref handling, unknown task IDs, and other edge cases.\n\nThe implementation appears complete—both mapping functions are in place with full test coverage. I'm wondering if the task might have been completed in a previous session, or if there's something specific still needed.\n\nRe-reading the task description, it asks to \"Implement task and unit mapping,\" but looking at the actual code, this appears to already be done. The test file exists with comprehensive coverage, and the adapter implementation is solid. Let me verify whether the tests actually pass before assuming everything is finished.\n</think>\n\nThe adapter code looks already implemented. Let me verify the tests pass and check if there's anything missing.\n\n\n\n","time":{"start":1778783721378,"end":1778783728806}}}
